Executive Profile
Richard F. Wallman  Independent Director, Roper Technologies, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 12 Board Members in 12 different organizations across 17 different industries.See Board Relationships66$744,820
Background

		Mr. Richard F. Wallman served as the Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President at Honeywell International Inc. since July 23, 2003 and served in the same positions from March 1995 to June 23, 2003. Mr. Wallman served as the Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President at AlliedSignal from 1995 to 1999. He held positions with IBM Corporation, Chrysler Corporation and Ford Motor Company. From April 1994 to March 1995, he served as a Vice President and Controller ... of International Business Machines Corp., and General Assistant Controller from 1993 to 1994. He began his career at Ford Motor Company in its finance and product development groups. Mr. Wallman served in a variety of finance positions with Chrysler Corporation, including Assistant Controller for Sales and Marketing. He served as a Vice President and the Controller of IBM Corporation. He is a Director of Accriva Diagnostics Holdings, Inc. and Bausch & Lomb Holdings Incorporated. He has been an Independent Director of Convergys Corporation since June 26, 2007. He has been an Independent Director of Charles River Laboratories International, Inc. since January 2011. He serves as a Director of HLI Operating Company, Inc., Accriva Diagnostics Holdings, Inc., RMI Corporation, Huber and Neteffect Corporation. He has been a Non-Executive Director at Wright Medical Group N.V. since October 2015. He has been a Non-Executive Director at Tornier, Inc. since December 2008 and a Director at Bausch & Lomb Incorporated since February 2008. He has been a Director of Extended Stay America, Inc. since July 2013 and Bausch & Lomb Holdings Incorporated since 2008. He has been Independent Director at Roper Technologies, Inc. since January 12, 2007. He served as a Director at Breakaway Solutions, Inc. since November 2000 and a Non-Executive Director at Tornier N.V. since December 2008. He served as a Director of Lear Corp., from November 13, 2003 to November 9, 2009 and Ariba Inc. from October 2002 to October 1, 2012. Mr. Wallman served as a Director of Expressjet Airlines, Inc., a subsidiary of Expressjet Holdings Inc. since January 2004. He served as a Director of Dana Holding Corporation from May 2010 to August 2013. He served as an Independent Director of Hayes Lemmerz International Inc., (a/k/a, Maxion Wheels Inc.) since 2003. Mr. Wallman served as a Director of Avaya Inc. from December 12, 2003 to October 26, 2007 and ExpressJet Holdings Inc. from January 2, 2004 to July 1, 2007. He served as a Director of CoreExpress, Inc. While at Honeywell, he was recognized by CFO Magazine as Chief Financial Officer of the Year for the category of Training and Building a Financial Team. Mr. Wallman holds a Master of Business Administration from the University Of Chicago Booth School Of Business with concentrations in Finance and Accounting and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Electrical Engineering from Vanderbilt University.Read Full Background




